About Ondo (ONDO)

What is Ondo (ONDO)?
Ondo (ONDO) is a decentralized cryptocurrency, launched in 2021 by Ondo Finance’s Nathan Allman and Pinku Suran. The duo launched Ondo Finance to make high-level financial tools that are typically reserved for big institutions, like banks, accessible to regular people. By using blockchain technology, ONDO connects traditional finance (TradFi), like banks and investments, with DeFi. This way, anyone can benefit from secure and innovative financial products.
How does the ONDO Token power Ondo Finance?
The ONDO token helps fuel the platform by enabling transactions and supporting Ondo's innovative financial products, like tokenized U.S. treasuries (OUSG) and dollar-yielding assets (USDY). ONDO also incentivizes users to participate in the ecosystem, whether through staking, lending, or borrowing.
What makes ONDO token compatible with Ethereum?
Compatible with the Ethereum network, ONDO, pronounced “On-doh,” is an ERC-20 token. You can use ONDO to trade and stake digital currencies, as well as participate in the Ethereum network. Ondo Finance’s ecosystem is powered by technology called smart contracts.
How do smart contracts work in Ethereum?
A smart contract is a digital agreement written in computer code that lives on Ethereum blockchain. It automatically does something when certain conditions are met. For example, if you send me 1 ONDO, the smart contract instantly sends you a digital artwork that I created. No human needs to be there to make it work; the smart contract follows the rules it was programmed with.
Why Is the Ethereum blockchain important for ONDO?
The Ethereum blockchain network that the ONDO token is compatible with is a huge, secure, ever-growing ledger of smart contract transactions, which everyone can see, and is immutable. Once a traditional smart contract is created, it can't be altered. These types of smart contracts will always follow the original rules that they were programmed with. Upgradable smart contracts allow for changes to be made, adapting to new requirements, or fixing bugs.
What are the popular use cases for ONDO?
Today, decentralized finance (DeFi) dapps are the most popular use for ONDO. ONDO token owners are typically community-driven investors and participants in DeFi protocols.

  • How do I bridge Ondo Finance (ONDO)?

    Bridging crypto across chains allows you to move tokens from one network to another. With MetaMask, bridging Ondo Finance (ONDO) is easy, secure, and cost-effective. Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging one token from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap one token from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.

  • What can you do with Ondo Finance (ONDO)?

    With Ondo Finance, you can send and receive ONDO, the network’s native token, and use it to pay transaction fees on certain networks. ONDO is supported in decentralized apps for trading, staking, payments, and NFTs. You can participate in DeFi protocols, bridge assets between networks, or use ONDO in select web3 games and marketplaces, all with Ethereum-compatible speed and flexibility.

  • How do I trade Ondo Finance for other cryptocurrencies?

    Trading ONDO for ETH, WBTC, or SOL can be done directly in MetaMask. For more information on how to swap ONDO, head to MetaMask Support’s ONDO Integration.
